, and estimated build time.\n        \"\"\"\n        # Analyze code efficiency\n        code_efficiency = self.code_analyzer.analyze_code(code)\n\n        # Add tasks to the task manager\n        for task in tasks:\n            task_id, dependencies = task\n            self.task_manager.add_task(task_id, dependencies)\n\n        # Get the order of tasks\n        task_order = self.task_manager.get_task_order()\n\n        # Estimate build time\n        estimated_build_time = self.time_estimator.estimate_build_time(len(tasks), code_efficiency)\n\n        # Return the results\n        return {\n            'code_efficiency': code_efficiency,\n            'task_order': task_order,\n            'estimated_build_time': estimated_build_time\n        }\n\n# Example usage\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    # Sample code and tasks\n    sample_code = \"import os\\nimport sys\\nprint('Hello, World!')\"\n    sample_tasks = [\n        ('task1', []),\n        ('task2', ['task1']),\n        ('task3', ['task1', 'task2'])\n    ]\n\n    # Create an instance of CollaborativeBuildOptimizer\n    cbo = CollaborativeBuildOptimizer()\n\n    # Optimize the build process\n    results = cbo.optimize_build(sample_code, sample_tasks)\n\n    # Print the results\n    print(\"Code Efficiency Analysis:\", results['code_efficiency'])\n    print(\"Task Order:\", results['task_order'])\n    print(\"Estimated Build Time:\", results['estimated_build_time'], \"hours\")", "suggestion": "LOCATION: `CodeEfficiencyAnalyzer` class\nISSUE: The `CodeEfficiencyAnalyzer` class is missing the implementation for the `analyze_code` method, which is crucial for performing code efficiency analysis.\nSUGGESTION: Implement the `analyze_code` method to analyze the code for common inefficiencies such as unused imports, redundant code, and inefficient algorithms. This can be done using static analysis tools or by writing custom logic to parse and evaluate the code.", "strategy": {"strategies": [{"action": "add", "target": {"