l serve as a starting point for further development, review, and optimization.\n\nHere is the initial implementation of `solution.py`:\n\n```json\n{\n  "solution.py": "import logging\\nfrom typing import List, Dict\\n\\nclass TaskManager:\\n    def __init__(self, tasks: Dict[str, List[str]]):\\n        self.tasks = tasks\\n\\n    def get_task_order(self) -> List[str]:\\n        in_degree = {u: 0 for u in self.tasks}\\n        for u in self.tasks:\\n            for v in self.tasks[u]:\\n                in_degree[v] += 1\\n        queue = [u for u in in_degree if in_degree[u] == 0]\\n        topo_order = []\\n        while queue:\\n            u = queue.pop(0)\\n            topo_order.append(u)\\n            for v in self.tasks[u]:\\n                in_degree[v] -= 1\\n                if in_degree[v] == 0:\\n                    queue.append(v)\\n        if len(topo_order) == len(self.tasks):\\n            return topo_order\\n        else:\\n            raise ValueError(\'Cycle detected in the task graph\')\\n\\n\\nclass GameEngine:\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        self.tasks = {}\\n        self.task_manager = TaskManager(self.tasks)\\n\\n    def add_task(self, task_name: str, dependencies: List[str] = None):\\n        if dependencies is None:\\n            dependencies = []\\n        self.tasks[task_name] = dependencies\\n        self.task_manager = TaskManager(self.tasks)\\n\\n    def execute_tasks(self):\\n        task_order = self.task_manager.get_task_order()\\n        for task in task_order:\\n            self.execute_task(task)\\n\\n    def execute_task(self, task_name: str):\\n        logging.info(f\'Executing task: {task_name}\')\\n        # Placeholder for task execution logic\\n\\n\\ndef main():\\n    game_engine = GameEngine()\\n    game_engine.add_task(\'initialize_game\', [])\\n    game_engine.add_task(\'load_assets\', [\'initialize_game\'])\\n    game_engine.add_task(\'setup_ui\', [\'load_assets\'])\\n    game_engine.add_task(\'start_game_loop\', [\'setup_ui\'])\\n    game_engine.execute_tasks()\\n\\nif __name__ == \'__main__\':\\n    logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)\\n    main()\\n"\n}\n```\n\nThis initial implementation includes a `TaskManager` class to handle task dependencies and a `GameEngine` class to manage game tasks. The `main` function sets up a basic task flow for initializing the game, loading assets, setting up the user interface, and starting the game loop. This can be expanded and refined as the development process progresses.', 'continue_simulation': True, 'communications': [], 'total_milestones': 0, 'agent_kpis': {}}], 'planning_scores': [-1, -1, -1, -1, -1], 'communication_scores': [-1, -1, -1, -1, -1], 'token_usage': 127706, 'agent_kpis': {}, 'total_milestones': 0}
